headline: Flight cuts, consumer sentiment, Miran speech: What to Watch
summary: Market Domination Overtime host Josh Lipton takes a look at the top stories for investors to watch on Friday, Nov. 7. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) announced a 10% decrease in air traffic, going into effect on Friday at 40 major airports. More commentary is coming from several Federal Reserve officials, including New York Fed President John Williams and Fed Governor Stephen Miran. Constellation Energy (CEG), Enbridge (ENB), and Duke Energy (DUK) will report quarterly results in the morning. The University of Michigan's preliminary November consumer sentiment reading will be posted in the morning. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Market Domination Overtime.

headline: S&P 500 Nuclear Leader Misses On Earnings. The Stock Is Falling Below A Buy Point.
summary: S&P 500 nuclear component Constellation Energy on Friday reported worse-than-expected third-quarter profit and narrowed its full-year earnings guidance.  Constellation Energy reported Q3 earnings growing nearly 11% to $3.04 per share while revenue totaled $6.57 billion, running basically flat vs. a year earlier.  The nuclear energy company also narrowed its 2025 adjusted earnings guidance to $9.05-$9.45 per share.

headline: Constellation Energy shares fall as Q3 earnings miss expectations
summary: Investing.com -- Constellation Energy Corporation (NASDAQ:CEG) reported third-quarter adjusted earnings of $3.04 per share, falling short of analyst expectations of $3.09, despite revenue of $6.57 billion exceeding the consensus estimate of $6.46 billion. The company’s shares dropped 3.1% premarket following the earnings miss.
